billion /ˈbɪljən/

(billions) 

1. NUM A billion is a thousand million. 10亿 

例： The Ethiopian foreign debt stands at 3 billion dollars. 埃塞俄比亚的外债达30亿美元。 

2. QUANT-PLURAL If you talk about billions of people or things, you mean that there is a very large number of them but you do not know or do not want to say exactly how many. 亿万 [QUANT 'of' pl-n] 

例： Biological systems have been doing this for billions of years. 生物系统亿万年来都在这样做。 

3. PRON You can also use billions as a pronoun. 亿万 

例： He thought that it must be worth billions. 他认为它一定值亿万元。 

4.  →  see also trillion

